element.name: Radio Ga Ga by AbbeyAckbar, Traditional Cache (1.5/1.5)

description.p: This cache is located near the Martello tower in Howth, which overlooks the harbour.
The tower is home to the Museum of Vintage Radio.

long-description.p: It is well worth a visit inside. The interior is crammed with antiques and memorabilia from days gone by. You can look around at your leisure or the guide can give you a tour around, showing you how some of the treasures work!
The walk up to the tower, from Abbey St., is brief but steep.
The cache is a micro, containing the log only, so bring your own pen and PLEASE replace the cache exactly were you found it.

We looked for this cache during our holidays in Ireland. Six fantastic days, 1800kms driven, and a bunch of caches found. Definitely a great way to get to know this beautiful island!
After eating an ice cream near the harbour, we went to find the cache. Nice view over there.
Thanks for this one... Greetings from Portugal
